    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Warren Raymond, Islandia’s founding father, spearheaded the village’s creation to gain local control over zoning and taxes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Islandia,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village’s heart began with a 500‑home Levitt & Sons development built around 1963.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Islandia%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A former CA Technologies campus, once a tech hub, was demolished in 2024 after the company moved to New York City.",
